Nehawu's Eastern Cape Secretary, Miki Jaceni speaks to #eNCA​ Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The National Education, Health and Allied Workers' Union says it's not prepared to work with Eastern Cape Health MEC, Sindiswa Gomba. Gomba is accused of involvement in a R10-million fraud, corruption and money laundering case, in connection with Nelson Mandela's funeral. READ: Mandela funeral scandal: Health MEC out on bail Nehawu's Eastern Cape secretary, Miki Jaceni says this is embarrassing. "We are embarrassed by the MEC appearing in court. We know that even if she continues in that department, she will no longer be able to deliver. We respect the rule of law, and also she is innocent until proven guilty by a court. We cannot interfere with what the Premier will do. What we are saying, for that department, with all the challenges, we cannot be able to work with her going forward." Eastern Cape Premier Oscar Mabuyane said the charges against his health MEC are serious, and he will make a decision soon. Watch the video above for more details on this story.